item.title: Java集合速览
item.description: A quick review of Java Collection and Map key methods. Array based collections usually have: Method Time complexity add O(1) insert(int index) O(N) remove O(1) remove(int index) O(N) find(Object value) O(N) PriorityQueue, TreeSet and TreeMap are implemented based on balanced tree, thus: Method Time complexity offer O(logN) poll O(logN) peek O(1) Overview via a diagram Collections extends Iterable which has below key methods: Method Description boolean hasNext() This method returns true if the iterator has more elements.
